<item>
            <title>[SOLR-6006] Separate test and compile scope dependencies in the Solrj and Solr contrib ivy.xml files, so that the derived Maven dependencies get filled out properly in the corresponding POMs</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-6006</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m not sure what version this first appeared in, as we just bumped from 4.5 to 4.7, but log4j is specified as a dependency in the solr-solrj pom.xml, and without the optional flag. I checked out the source to verify that there isn&apos;t actually a dependency on log4j (doesn&apos;t seem to be), but I wasn&apos;t able to decipher the ant build (looks like there&apos;s a pom.xml.template that generates the pom with dependencies coming from Ivy?)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Anyway, this is an issue since now we have to manually &amp;lt;exclude&amp;gt; log4j from every project that depends on SolrJ.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
